484
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:37,000
by using set theory and then realized, oh, crap.

485
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:40,000
Set theory as we've been using it is inconsistent.

486
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:42,000
What do we do?

487
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:46,000
Well, they addressed this in a variety of ways.

488
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,000
Russell developed the theory of types.

489
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:50,000
He was talking about objects and then classes of objects

490
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,000
and classes of classes of objects

491
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:55,000
and classes of classes of objects and so on.

492
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:58,000
And that's one way of approaching it.

493
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:01,000
Kline himself developed something called new foundations

494
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:03,000
that tried to prevent any circularities

495
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:06,000
and thought the problem was really the X belongings

496
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:08,000
who were not belonging to X,

497
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:11,000
ruling such things out as illegitimate.

498
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:16,000
