504
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,000
with a bunch of other principles.

505
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:39,000
It restricts this to say you can only do this within a certain background set.

506
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:42,000
So you can define a new set inside another set,

507
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:44,000
but not just out of thin air.

508
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:46,000
It says pairs of things.

509
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:49,000
You can basically, if you have two objects, X and Y,

510
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,000
you can have the pair set X, Y.

511
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:55,000
You can take the power set of a set, the set of all the subsets and so on.

512
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:58,000
